

     ___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

                                                                        CDR-Stats : REQUIREMENTS
     ___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________



  Python 2.6 >=


* Add repository on CentOS 5.4 
--------------------------------

	i386:
		rpm -Uvh http://download.fedora.redhat.com/pub/epel/5/i386/epel-release-5-3.noarch.rpm
	x86_64:
		rpm -Uvh http://download.fedora.redhat.com/pub/epel/5/x86_64/epel-release-5-3.noarch.rpm



* Install Git 
---------------

	yum install git



* Install django
------------------

    http://www.djangoproject.com/download/
    
    First, download Django-1.2.1.tar.gz. 
        wget wget http://www.djangoproject.com/download/1.2.1/tarball/
    
    Then,
        tar xzvf Django-1.2.1.tar.gz
        cd Django-1.2.1
        sudo python setup.py install



* django-debug-toolbar
------------------------

	download :
	    wget http://github.com/robhudson/django-debug-toolbar/tarball/0.8.2
	
	install :
	    tar -xvzf robhudson-django-debug-toolbar-0.8.2-0-g55b5a77.tar.gz 
	    cd robhudson-django-debug-toolbar-55b5a77/
	    sudo python setup.py install
	    sudo rm -rf build/ dist django_debug_toolbar.egg-info/



* django-dilla 
----------------
    
    inside the cdr-stats directory :
	    http://github.com/areski/django-dilla/tarball/master


* django-extensions
-----------------------

	Download sources :
	    svn checkout http://django-command-extensions.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ django-command-extensions
	
	Then install:
        sudo python setup.py install
        
        # very useful to generate graph :
            # Create a PNG image file called my_project_visualized.png with application grouping
            python manage.py graph_models -a -g -o my_project_visualized.png


* python-dateutil
-------------------

    Install :
        sudo easy_install DateUtils


* Django-uni-form
----------------------

    install :
    sudo easy_install django-uni-form >= 0.8.0
    http://github.com/areski/django-uni-form/tarball/0.8.0


* South
-------------
    
    install :
    sudo easy_install South


* BluePrint 
-------------
    
    Css framework : Blueprint
    this is included
    
    


